HEADWORD: Resentingly
<hw>Re*sent"ing*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>With deep
sense or strong perception.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dr. H.
More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With a sense of wrong or affront; with
resentment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resentive</ent>⟦br⟧
